description:
Bye bye 2020!
Thanks Thanks Friends - Family - Fans - Sponsors.
The 2020 a very hard & dark year for almost everyone. A year that we were slaves and not free, to feel controlled by a bunch of clowns. We have fought almost every day for our jobs, bussiness, see childrens following ridiculous  school class on a screen meanwhile watching the world fall down. I have seen many friends had a very bad time with medical, financial and personal issues ... but we have moved forward, we have done miracles to survive. 
Friends have been friends, family has been family and we have come against all odds to 2021. THank #god 2020 is almost gone, letâ€™s hope and pray to God that 2021 will be a #possitive year to everyone and thanks you #friends & #family for being there! #BigSupport 
For 2021 we are the same humble, honest, sincere, friend of friends, always you are going to be welcome with a hug!

â£Most difficult race weekend of the seasonğŸ Since Porsche Carrera Cup was competing at Falkenberg today we look back to the Formula STCC race there in 2017.â €
â €
We learnt loads during the practice but I didnâ€™t manage to get a great feeling for the car. We did some changes ahead of the qualifying and improved a bit to grab P4 and P3.â €
â €
Starting fourth in the first race I snatched P2 after a couple of great battles. The second race was an interesting one as well with plenty of fights and a safety car in the middle. Made a big launch after the safety car and managed to secure second place again.â €
â €
All in all an we were lacking pace but managed great results regardless.â €

â €
In race 1 we saw an incident immediately on the starting straight, but were able to continue relatively unharmed. After fighting off Villeneuve and keeping up the pace we finished the race in 5th place.â €
â €
As we lined up for Race 2 the skies suddenly opened and everyone swapped to wet tires. Struggling with pace initially, due to limited wet experience, I improved throughout the race and eventually brought the car home in 6th position.â €

caption: Photo by Joakim Jardenberg in Ring Knutstorp with @hugonerman.
description:
"I don't know better, I only know different" Mentoring is great, reversed mentoring is better. So it's truly my privilege to be the  mentor/mentee of Hugo Nerman, a young racecar driver from my hometown Helsingborg. I learn so much from him. 
Today it's his premiere in #STCC, and after a great qualification yesterday I really look forward to the two races this afternoon. Another step for Hugo, towards becoming world champion in F1. I have no doubt that's where he'll end up. 
#anotherthingtoday #hugonerman #tcr
